{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"93fbcd85-5289-4540-9499-da62523c0961","content":"Here are the common options depending on your stack:\n\n**ASP.NET Core (dotnet)**\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth Individual   # Identity-based (local accounts)\ndotnet new webapi --auth IndividualB2C # Azure AD B2C\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg    # Azure AD (single tenant)\ndotnet new webapi --auth MultiOrg     # Azure AD (multi-tenant)\ndotnet new webapi --auth Windows      # Windows/Negotiate auth\n```\n\n**Node.js** — Express + Passport.js, or Fastify with JWT/OAuth plugins.\n\n**Python** — FastAPI with OAuth2/JWT, or Django REST Framework with token auth.\n\n**Java** — Spring Boot with Spring Security (`spring-boot-starter-oauth2-resource-server`).\n\nFor most new .NET projects, `dotnet new webapi --auth Individual` is a solid starting point. Want me to scaffold one for you?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"06fe22db-0f64-4f2d-846f-d9e72dd58eae","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking a general knowledge question about web API project templates and authentication options. This doesn't require any tool calls - I can answer from my knowledge of common web frameworks.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer covering the main options.","outputTokens":289,"requestId":"C812:3F1DAE:6D1BAD1:755E505:6A03CBB4"},"id":"cbaa69ea-1182-4ede-9c40-245101e7fe0b","timestamp":"2026-05-13T00:54:20.174Z","parentId":"a556cb4d-cb74-45a9-b14c-872a1e9629e8"}
